cells.name: Network

queries.query: SELECT non_negative_derivative(max("bytes_recv"), 1s) AS "received", non_negative_derivative(max("bytes_sent"), 1s) AS "sent" FROM "telegraf"."autogen"."net" WHERE time > :dashboardTime:  GROUP BY time(:interval:) FILL(null)

queryConfig.rawText: SELECT non_negative_derivative(max("bytes_recv"), 1s) AS "received", non_negative_derivative(max("bytes_sent"), 1s) AS "sent" FROM "telegraf"."autogen"."net" WHERE time > :dashboardTime:  GROUP BY time(:interval:) FILL(null)

cells.note: To enable this graph, you will need to configure the Telegraf `net` plugin. For more information, please visit the [Telegraf Net plugin documentation](https://github.com/influxdata/telegraf/tree/master/plugins/inputs/net).

cells.name: CPU Utilization %

queries.query: SELECT mean("usage_system") AS "system", mean("usage_user") as "user", mean("usage_iowait") as "iowait", mean("usage_idle") as "idle"  FROM "telegraf"."autogen"."cpu" WHERE time > :dashboardTime: AND "cpu"='cpu-total' GROUP BY time(:interval:) FILL(null)

cells.note: To enable this graph, you will need to configure the Telegraf `cpu` plugin. For more information, please visit the [Telegraf CPU plugin documentation](https://github.com/influxdata/telegraf/tree/master/plugins/inputs/cpu).

cells.name: System Load

queries.query: SELECT mean("load1") AS "load1", mean("load5") AS "load5", mean("load15") AS "load15" FROM "telegraf"."autogen"."system" WHERE time > :dashboardTime:  GROUP BY time(:interval:) FILL(null)

cells.note: To enable this graph, you will need to configure the Telegraf `system` plugin. For more information, please visit the [Telegraf System plugin documentation](https://github.com/influxdata/telegraf/tree/master/plugins/inputs/system).
